revision.text: ==English== ===Etymology=== From the {{bor|en|cmn-wadegile|-}} romanization of the {{uder|en|cmn|-}} Chinese pronunciation for {{zh-l|葉|tr=Yeh⁴}}. ===Proper noun=== {{en-proper noun|Yehs}} # {{surname|en}}. ===Statistics=== * According to the 2010 United States Census, ''Yeh'' is the 5046<sup>th</sup> most common surname in the United States, belonging to 6958 individuals. ''Yeh'' is most common among Asian/Pacific Islander (92.8%) individuals. ===Anagrams=== * {{anagrams|en|a=ehy|Hey|hey|hye}}
